<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.48/376: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-12T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            12, 1920—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>866. Your 1179, August 5, 4 P.M.</p>
                            <p>Department agrees with views expressed in last paragraph of your
                                telegram and has today indicated to Director of European Children’s
                                Fund that it is Department’s desire that no member of their
                                organization remain in territory under Bolshevik occupation. You may
                                so inform Brown who will be advised directly by New York Office.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>